GENEVA , July 10 -LRB- Xinhua -RRB- -- Swiss scientists have made important headway recently in the research of the transmissible agent of mad cow disease , local press reported today .
Two research groups of the Institute for Molecular Biology and Biophysics of Zurich University have succeeded in finding out the three-dimensional structure of a fragment of the so-called prion protein , which among other things can cause mad cow disease .
Reports said this important finding , achieved by the use of nuclear magnetic resonance spectroscope , provides interesting insight in the function and structure of prion molecule .
